# Pixel Puncher 

**Team Members: Whising** [Your names here]

**How would you pitch your game in one line?**
Basically a 2d Platformer with exciting maps and abilities!

**What is the key mechanic(s) that make it fun?**
Various different levels that are designed so that the abilities like punching can be used, you can also use coins to collect more abilities!

**How does the game actually play? (Core Game Loop)**
Basic 2d Platformer with 30-35 levels each getting harder every time you progress to a new level! Of course while collecting new abilities.

**How will you keep players engaged for 30 minutes? What's the general scope of your game (will change as you go)?**
My main focus of the game is engaging gameplay for a fun relaxing time, while being challenging! This can usually be used to make players engaged for very long times!

---
*Remember: Focus on gameplay mechanics and player experience. Save the details about story, art style, sound design, UI flowcharts, marketing plans, or achievements for later.*
